## Status

| Value | Description |
|---|---|
| `Draft` | Editable. Initial state and state after rejection or withdrawal. |
| `PendingApproval` | Publication requested; reviewers assigned. Writes blocked until review concludes. |
| `Published` | Approved. Item is live. Requires Withdraw to return to Draft. |
| `Revising` | Owner is preparing a new version. Published version remains live for readers. All edit operations (metadata, assets) allowed. Publish transitions to PendingApproval or Published (v+1). |
| `Archived` | Terminal. No further operations permitted. |

## Status transitions

```
Draft ──Publish (no reviewers)──► Published (immediate)
Draft ──Publish (with reviewers)─► PendingApproval ──all approve──► Published
                                                    ──any rejects──► Draft
Published ──Withdraw──► Draft
Published ──BeginRevision──► Revising ──Publish──► PendingApproval → Published (v+1)
                                      ──DiscardRevision──► Published (draft discarded)
PendingApproval ──Withdraw──► Draft
Draft / Published / PendingApproval ──Archive──► Archived
```

## Review lifecycle

Review is managed inline on MediaItem via an embedded `ReviewSession` value object.

### BeginRevision
- `Status` must be `Published`
- Transitions to `Revising`
- Initialises `Metadata.Draft` from `Metadata.Current` (edits start from published content)
- Published version remains live and readable

### DiscardRevision
- `Status` must be `Revising`
- Discards all draft changes (`Metadata.Draft` cleared)
- Returns to `Published` (published version and version number unchanged)

### Publish
User intent is to publish. If no reviewers assigned → publishes immediately. If reviewers assigned → item enters `PendingApproval` state until all approve.

- `Status` must be `Draft`
- All required metadata fields must be present
- All required asset roles must be filled with Active assets
- `ReviewerIds` empty → publishes immediately, item transitions directly to `Published`
- `ReviewerIds` non-empty → `Status` → `PendingApproval`, `ReviewSession` created with all reviewers in `Pending` state

### ApproveReview (reviewer action)
- `Status` must be `PendingApproval`
- Caller must be a reviewer in the active `ReviewSession`
- Reviewer must not have already decided
- Records `Approved` decision for the reviewer
- When all non-withdrawn reviewers have approved → item transitions to `Published`, `CurrentVersionNumber` increments

### RejectReview (reviewer action)
- `Status` must be `PendingApproval`
- Caller must be a reviewer in the active `ReviewSession`
- Reviewer must not have already decided
- `Reason` required (non-empty)
- Item immediately transitions to `Draft`. Draft metadata preserved for revision.

### ReviewSession
Embedded value object on MediaItem. Contains:
- `ReviewSessionId` — unique per submit cycle
- `CommentThreadId` (nullable) — reference to a `MediaChangeRequest` comment thread
- `Reviewers` — list of `ReviewerAssignment` (`ReviewerId`, `Decision`, `AssignedAt`, `DecidedAt`)
- `StartedAt`

