## Handler-side Pre-conditions

| Handler | Service | Guard type | Condition |
|---|---|---|---|
| `CreateMediaItemHandler` | `IMediaProfileQueryService.GetPublishedAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Profile must exist and be published. Handler calls `media-profile.CompiledTemplate.ToSnapshot()` to produce `MediaProfileSnapshot`, and builds `snapshotRecordTypeVersions` from `media-profile.RecordTypeRefs`. Both are passed to `MediaItem.Create(...)` and embedded in `MediaItemCreated`. The aggregate never fetches media-profile data directly. |
| `CreateMediaItemHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Only when `command.FolderId` is set; media-folder must be active; derives `CollectionId` passed to `MediaItem.Create(...)` |
| `CreateMediaItemHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.NameExistsInScopeAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Only when `command.FolderId` is set; rejects if the title is already in use within that media-folder scope. See [Cross-Aggregate Constraint Enforcement](../../../../../shared/system-spec.md#cross-aggregate-constraint-enforcement). |
| `AssignMediaItemToFolderHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Before loading aggregate; media-folder must be active; derived `CollectionId` passed to `mediaItem.AssignToFolder(...)` |
| `AssignMediaItemToFolderHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.NameExistsInScopeAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After `GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` passes; rejects if the media-item's current title is already in use within the target media-folder scope. |
| `MoveMediaItemHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` | Blocking — `ResourceNotFound` | Before loading aggregate; media-folder must be active; derived `CollectionId` passed to `mediaItem.Move(...)` |
| `MoveMediaItemHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.NameExistsInScopeAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After `GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` passes; rejects if the media-item's current title is already in use within the target media-folder scope. |
| `UpdateMediaItemTitleHandler` | `IFolderQueryService.NameExistsInScopeAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Only when `mediaItem.IsAssignedToFolder()`; rejects if the new title is already in use within the current media-folder scope |
| `AssignAssetToRoleHandler` | `IMediaProfileQueryService.GetPublishedAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After loading aggregate; validates role exists in `AssetDefinitions` and asset `ContentType` is accepted; checks `AllowMultiple` constraint; returns `RoleAlreadyFilled` if `AllowMultiple = false` and role already occupied |
| `AssignAssetToRoleHandler` | `IAssetQueryService.GetAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After role definition check; asset must exist and be `Active`; `ContentType` must match role's `AcceptedContentTypes` |
| `ReplaceAssetInRoleHandler` | `IMediaProfileQueryService.GetPublishedAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After loading aggregate; validates role exists and `AllowMultiple = false` (replace semantics are single-slot only); returns `RoleNotFilled` if no asset currently assigned to the role |
| `ReplaceAssetInRoleHandler` | `IAssetQueryService.GetAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | New asset must exist and be `Active`; `ContentType` must match role's `AcceptedContentTypes` |
| `PublishMediaItemHandler` | `IMediaProfileQueryService.GetPublishedAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | After loading aggregate; media-profile must exist; checks all required asset roles are filled. |
| `PublishMediaItemHandler` | `IAssetQueryService.GetManyAsync` | Blocking — `InvalidOperation` | Batch-fetches all assigned media-assets; any asset not `Active` blocks publication |
| `ApproveReviewHandler` | `IAssetQueryService.GetManyAsync` | Enrichment — non-blocking (missing refs produce null storage keys) | Batch-fetches storage keys for all assigned assets; used to build `ApprovedAssetSnapshot` list passed to `mediaItem.ApproveReview(...)`. Assets not found in the reference model produce snapshots with null storage fields. |

