## Constraint Enforcement — Implementation Notes

### `IFolderQueryService` Implementation

`GetActiveCollectionIdAsync` queries `media-folders`. `NameExistsInScopeAsync` queries `media-name-reservations` using scope key `FOLDER#{FolderId}` — distinct from the media-folder child-name scope (`PARENT#{...}`) used by `IFolderHierarchyService`.

```csharp
sealed class FolderQueryService(IAmazonDynamoDB dynamo) : IFolderQueryService
{
    /// Returns the media-folder's CollectionId, or null if not found or archived.
    /// Used by Create, Assign, and Move handlers to derive CollectionId without
    /// exposing the Folder aggregate to the MediaItem write model.
    public async Task<CollectionId?> GetActiveCollectionIdAsync(
        TenantId tenantId, FolderId folderId, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        var response = await dynamo.GetItemAsync(new GetItemRequest
        {
            TableName = "media-folders",
            Key = DynamoKey.For(tenantId, folderId),
            ProjectionExpression = "CollectionId, IsArchived"
        }, ct);
        if (!response.IsItemSet) return null;
        if (response.Item["IsArchived"].BOOL) return null;
        return new CollectionId(response.Item["CollectionId"].S);
    }

    /// Returns true if the given title is already in use within the media-folder.
    /// Scope key: FOLDER#{FolderId} — covers MediaItem titles only.
    /// Distinct from IFolderHierarchyService.NameExistsInScopeAsync which covers
    /// child media-folder names under PARENT#{...}.
    /// ConsistentRead = true — reservation written by a concurrent handler is immediately visible.
    public async Task<bool> NameExistsInScopeAsync(
        TenantId tenantId, FolderId folderId, string name, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        var key = NameReservationKey.For(
            tenantId, $"FOLDER#{folderId}", name.Trim().ToLowerInvariant());
        var response = await dynamo.GetItemAsync(new GetItemRequest
        {
            TableName = "media-name-reservations",
            Key = key,
            ConsistentRead = true
        }, ct);
        return response.IsItemSet; // true = title already in use within this media-folder
    }
}
```

All handlers call `repository.Save(mediaItem)` and `nameReservationService.Reserve(intent)` — both register with the ambient `ITransactionScope` and are committed atomically by the MediatR `TransactionBehavior`. `NameReservationConflictException` is handled by the `NameReservationConflictBehavior`; handlers never catch it directly.

Intent per operation: `CreateMediaItemHandler` → `NameReservation.Reserve(tenantId, MediaItemTitle(folderId), title)`. `AssignMediaItemToFolderHandler` → `NameReservation.Reserve(tenantId, MediaItemTitle(targetFolderId), title)`. `MoveMediaItemHandler` → `NameReservation.Move(tenantId, MediaItemTitle(oldFolderId), MediaItemTitle(newFolderId), title)`. `UpdateMediaItemTitleHandler` → `NameReservation.Swap(tenantId, MediaItemTitle(folderId), oldTitle, newTitle)`. `ArchiveMediaItemHandler` → `NameReservation.Release(tenantId, MediaItemTitle(folderId), title)`.

For the canonical handler structure see [Collection — Constraint Enforcement](../Collection/media-collection.write-model.md#constraint-enforcement--implementation-notes).

