## Reference Models

Reference models consumed by this write model's command handlers. All are read-only projections; this context never writes to them directly.

---

### `media-profiles` (DynamoDB — published slice)

**Owned by:** Catalog (same context — internal projection)
**Consumed via:** `IMediaProfileQueryService` (`GetPublishedAsync`)
**Used by:** `CreateMediaItemHandler` (snapshot embed + RecordTypeRefs), `AssignAssetToRoleHandler` (role validation), `PublishMediaItemHandler` (required roles).

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `MediaProfileId` | `string` | Lookup key |
| `Status` | `string` | Must be `Published` — null return from `GetPublishedAsync` blocks the operation |
| `CompiledTemplate` | `object` | Embedded into `MediaItemCreated` as `MediaProfileSnapshot` |
| `AssetDefinitions` | `AssetDefinition[]` | Role existence check, `ContentType` acceptance, `AllowMultiple` constraint |
| `RecordTypeRefs` | `RecordTypeVersion[]` | Pinned `{RecordTypeId, Version}` pairs; embedded in snapshot |
| `Capabilities` | `CapabilitySet` | Capability checks |

**Subscribed events (same-context projection — `media-projector` SQS queue):**

| Event | Write |
|---|---|
| `MediaProfilePublished` | UPSERT all fields from `MediaProfilePublishedSnapshot` |
| `MediaProfileDeprecated` | UPDATE `Status = Deprecated` |

---

### `media-folders` (DynamoDB)

**Owned by:** Catalog (same context — internal projection)
**Consumed via:** `IFolderQueryService` (`GetActiveCollectionIdAsync`, `NameExistsInScopeAsync`)
**Used by:** `CreateMediaItemHandler`, `AssignMediaItemToFolderHandler`, `MoveMediaItemHandler` (derive `CollectionId`; never caller-supplied), `UpdateMediaItemTitleHandler` (title uniqueness in current media-folder). `NameExistsInScopeAsync` queries `media-name-reservations` (scope key `FOLDER#{FolderId}`).

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `FolderId` | `string` | Lookup key |
| `CollectionId` | `string` | Derived and passed to aggregate; callers never supply it |
| `IsArchived` | `bool` | Null return on archived media-folder blocks folder-targeting operations |

**Subscribed events (same-context projection — `media-projector` SQS queue):**

| Event | Write |
|---|---|
| `FolderCreated` | INSERT |
| `FolderMoved` | UPDATE `CollectionId` (if cross-collection move is ever permitted) |
| `FolderArchived` | UPDATE `IsArchived = true` |

---

### `media-assets` (DynamoDB — status/content-type slice)

**Owned by:** AssetManagement
**Consumed via:** `IAssetQueryService` (`GetAsync`, `GetManyAsync`)
**Used by:** `AssignAssetToRoleHandler` (asset must be `Active`; `ContentType` must match role), `PublishMediaItemHandler` (batch-fetches all assigned media-assets; any non-`Active` blocks publication).

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `AssetId` | `string` | Lookup key |
| `Status` | `AssetStatus` | Must be `Active` for assignment and review submission |
| `ContentType` | `MediaContentType` | Role `ContentType` acceptance check on assignment |
| `FileName` | `string?` | Original filename; captured at `AssetUploaded`. Used in `ApprovedAssetSnapshot`. |
| `SourceStorageKey` | `string?` | S3 key of the source object; captured at `AssetUploaded`. Used in `ApprovedAssetSnapshot`. |
| `Renditions` | `AssetRenditionRef[]` | `[{ RenditionType, StorageKey, ContentType }]`; populated on `AssetProcessingCompleted`. Empty for document (non-processing) assets. |

**Subscribed integration events (projector owned by Catalog, consuming AssetManagement via `media-projector` SQS queue):**

| Event | Write |
|---|---|
| `AssetUploaded` | INSERT with `Status = Pending`, `ContentType`, `FileName`, `SourceStorageKey = e.StorageKey` |
| `AssetValidationPassed` | UPDATE `Status = Active` (when no `Processing` capability — fast exit path) |
| `AssetProcessingCompleted` | UPDATE `Status = Active`, `Renditions`; preserve `FileName` and `SourceStorageKey` from current |
| `AssetValidationFailed` | UPDATE `Status = ValidationFailed` |
| `AssetProcessingFailed` | UPDATE `Status = ProcessingFailed`; preserve other fields |
| `AssetArchived` | UPDATE `Status = Archived` |
| `AssetDeleted` | UPDATE `Status = Deleted` |

